# PixelLink / Electron + MCP environment configuration
# Copy this file to `.env` (or export vars in your shell) and restart PixelLink.

# --- Runtime toggles (mostly used by the Electron bridge) ---
# PIXELINK_DRY_RUN=1
# PIXELINK_SPEED=1.0
# PIXELINK_ENABLE_KILL_SWITCH=0

# --- Google Calendar & Gmail (optional) ---
# Place credentials.json in the repo root, or set paths explicitly.
# On first run, a browser will open for OAuth; tokens are saved locally.
#
# Default (no env needed): credentials.json, token.json, token_gmail.json in repo root
# Or set:
# PIXELINK_CALENDAR_CREDENTIALS_PATH=/path/to/credentials.json
# PIXELINK_CALENDAR_TOKEN_PATH=/path/to/token.json
# PIXELINK_GMAIL_CREDENTIALS_PATH=/path/to/credentials.json
# PIXELINK_GMAIL_TOKEN_PATH=/path/to/token_gmail.json

# --- Notes/Reminders MCP (macOS only) ---
# No API keys needed. macOS will prompt for Automation permissions the first time.

# --- LLM Brain (optional) ---
# Used for intelligent responses when commands aren't recognized.
# Set in pylink/.env: OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key
# Optional: OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini (default)
